article.description: — Jackson Paveletzke had 21 points in Wofford's 78-64 victory against N.C. A&T on Sunday night.
article.headline: Paveletzke has 21 as Wofford takes down N.C. A&T 78-64
article.linkText: Paveletzke has 21 as Wofford takes down N.C. A&T 78-64
article.story: SPARTANBURG, S.C. -- — Jackson Paveletzke had 21 points in Wofford's 78-64 victory against N.C. A&T on Sunday night. Paveletzke had six assists for the Terriers (3-2). Jackson Sivills scored 13 points while shooting 5 for 6, including 3 for 4 from beyond the arc. B.J. Mack was 5 of 11 shooting (2 for 4 from distance) to finish with 12 points. Kam Woods led the Aggies (1-4) in scoring, finishing with 17 points. Marcus Watson added 16 points and four assists for N.C. A&T. In addition, Demetric Horton had 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
